race.comment: SHANGRI LA BOY (4) resumes after being nailed late by ATTICA when a gallant second in the G1 Champion Stakes over 2000m at Randwick last October. Expected to push forward and can run then off their feet with the three searching trials. Go close. NINJA (7) kept fresh and race fitness will take him a long way in his toughest test to date. Beaten by the wide draw and unlucky not to win on protest with a close-up second in the LR Magic Millions 3yo Guineas at Gold Coast over this trip. Kept up to the mark with a 1000m trial win and shapes as the main danger. AUTUMN BOY (1) Group 1 winning colt resuming. Wasn't knocked around in his two trials and the blinkers come off. Sure to be motoring late. NAPOLEONIC (5) excellent return on the fast tempo when second to Tempted over 1200m in the G3 Eskimo Prince Stakes at Randwick. Expected to get the trip and not without top-three claims.
